properties.areaDesc: Kaibab Plateau; Coconino Plateau; Little Colorado River Valley in Coconino County; Grand Canyon Country; Western Mogollon Rim
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued February 1 at 2:13PM MST until February 3 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Flagstaff AZ
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
possible. Localized gusts 65 to 70 mph possible near the San
Francisco peaks and the Doney Park area.

* WHERE...Much of Coconino County including the Kaibab Plateau,
Grand Canyon Village, Valle, Flagstaff, Doney Park.

* WHEN...From Sunday evening through late Sunday night.

* IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property
and cause power outages. Travel could be difficult especially
for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A period of snow showers is likely to
develop as the winds begin to decrease early Monday morning and
into the afternoon.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SUNDAY EVENING THROUGH LATE SUNDAY NIGHT
